accessAndSpendNotice.description: $1 is the url of the site requesting ability to spend

addCustomTokenByContractAddress.description: $1 is a blockchain explorer for a specific network, e.g. Etherscan for Ethereum

addEthereumChainConfirmationRisksLearnMo.description: $1 is a link with text that is provided by the 'addEthereumChainConfirmationRisksLearnMoreLink' key
Link text for the 'addEthereumChainConfirmationRisksLearnMore' translation key

allowOriginSpendToken.description: $1 is the url of the site and $2 is the symbol of the token they are requesting to spend

allowWithdrawAndSpend.description: The url of the site that requested permission to 'withdraw and spend'

approveSpendLimit.description: The token symbol that is being approved

blockExplorerView.description: $1 replaced by URL for custom block explorer

connectTo.description: $1 is the name/origin of a web3 site/application that the user can connect to metamask

connectToAll.description: $1 will be replaced by the translation of connectToAllAccounts

connectToAllAccounts.description: will replace $1 in connectToAll, completing the sentence 'connect to all of your accounts', will be text that shows list of accounts on hover

connectToMultiple.description: $1 will be replaced by the translation of connectToMultipleNumberOfAccounts

connectToMultipleNumberOfAccounts.description: $1 is the number of accounts to which the web3 site/application is asking to connect; this will substitute $1 in connectToMultiple

endOfFlowMessage7.description: $1 is a clickable link with text defined by the 'here' key. The link will open to a form where users can file support tickets.

endpointReturnedDifferentChainId.description: $1 is the return value of eth_chainId from an RPC endpoint

errorCode.description: Displayed error code for debugging purposes. $1 is the error code

errorDetails.description: Title for collapsible section that displays error details for debugging purposes

errorMessage.description: Displayed error message for debugging purposes. $1 is the error message

errorName.description: Displayed error name for debugging purposes. $1 is the error name

errorPageMessage.description: Message displayed on generic error page in the fullscreen or notification UI, $1 is a clickable link with text defined by the 'here' key. The link will open to a form where users can file support tickets.

errorPagePopupMessage.description: Message displayed on generic error page in the popup UI, $1 is a clickable link with text defined by the 'here' key. The link will open to a form where users can file support tickets.

errorStack.description: Title for error stack, which is displayed for debugging purposes

extraApprovalGas.description: Expresses an additional gas amount the user will have to pay, on top of some other displayed amount. $1 is a decimal amount of gas

fileImportFail.description: Helps user import their account from a JSON file

fromAddress.description: $1 is the address to include in the From label. It is typically shortened first using shortenAddress

gasLimitTooLowWithDynamicFee.description: $1 is the custom gas limit, in decimal.

gdprMessage.description: $1 refers to the gdprMessagePrivacyPolicy message, the translation of which is meant to be used exclusively in the context of gdprMessage

gdprMessagePrivacyPolicy.description: this translation is intended to be exclusively used as the replacement for the $1 in the gdprMessage translation

getEtherFromFaucet.description: Displays network name for Ether faucet

here.description: as in -click here- for more information (goes with troubleTokenBalances)

hideTokenSymbol.description: $1 is the symbol for a token (e.g. 'DAI')

import.description: Button to import an account from a selected file

importAccountText.description: $1 represents the text from `importAccountLinkText` as a link

imported.description: status showing that an account has been fully loaded into the keyring

infuraBlockedNotification.description: $1 is a clickable link with with text defined by the 'here' key

invalidCustomNetworkAlertContent1.description: $1 is the name/identifier of the network.

metametricsCommitmentsBoldNever.description: This string is localized separately from some of the commitments so that we can bold it

metametricsCommitmentsNeverCollectIP.description: The $1 is the bolded word 'Never', from 'metametricsCommitmentsBoldNever'

metametricsCommitmentsNeverCollectKeysEt.description: The $1 is the bolded word 'Never', from 'metametricsCommitmentsBoldNever'

metametricsCommitmentsNeverSellDataForPr.description: The $1 is the bolded word 'Never', from 'metametricsCommitmentsBoldNever'

mismatchedChain.description: $1 is a clickable link with text defined by the 'mismatchedChainLinkText' key

mismatchedChainLinkText.description: Serves as link text for the 'mismatchedChain' key. This text will be embedded inside the translation for that key.

needHelp.description: $1 represents `needHelpLinkText`, the text which goes in the help link

needImportFile.description: User is important an account and needs to add a file to continue

newAccountNumberName.description: Default name of next account to be created on create account screen

nextNonceWarning.description: The next nonce according to MistWallet's internal logic

notifications1Description.description: Description of a notification in the 'See What's New' popup. Describes the swapping on mobile feature.

notifications1Title.description: Title for a notification in the 'See What's New' popup. Tells users that they can now use MistWallet Swaps on Mobile.

notifications3ActionText.description: The 'call to action' on the button, or link, of the 'Stay secure' notification. Upon clicking, users will be taken to a page about security on the metamask support website.

notifications3Description.description: Description of a notification in the 'See What's New' popup. Describes the information they can get on security from the linked support page.

notifications3Title.description: Title for a notification in the 'See What's New' popup. Encourages users to consider security.

notifications4ActionText.description: The 'call to action' on the button, or link, of the 'Swap on Binance Smart Chain!' notification. Upon clicking, users will be taken to a page where then can swap tokens on Binance Smart Chain.

notifications4Description.description: Description of a notification in the 'See What's New' popup.

notifications4Title.description: Title for a notification in the 'See What's New' popup. Encourages users to do swaps on Binance Smart Chain.

notifications5Description.description: Description of a notification in the 'See What's New' popup. Describes the seed phrase wording update.

notifications6DescriptionTwo.description: Description of a notification in the 'See What's New' popup. Describes the Ledger support update.

notifications6Title.description: Title for a notification in the 'See What's New' popup. Lets users know about the Ledger support update

onboardingReturnNotice.description: Return the user to the site that initiated onboarding

pastePrivateKey.description: For importing an account from a private key

plusXMore.description: $1 is a number of additional but unshown items in a list- this message will be shown in place of those items

privateKey.description: select this type of file to use to import an account

restoreWalletPreferences.description: $1 is the date at which the data was backed up

spendLimitRequestedBy.description: Origin of the site requesting the spend limit

swapAllowSwappingOf.description: Shows a user that they need to allow a token for swapping on their hardware wallet

swapApproval.description: Used in the transaction display list to describe a transaction that is an approve call on a token that is to be swapped.. $1 is the symbol of a token that has been approved.

swapApproveNeedMoreTokens.description: Tells the user how many more of a given token they need for a specific swap. $1 is an amount of tokens and $2 is the token symbol.

swapBuildQuotePlaceHolderText.description: Tells the user that a given search string does not match any tokens in our token lists. $1 can be any string of text

swapEnableDescription.description: Gives the user info about the required approval transaction for swaps. $1 will be the symbol of a token being approved for swaps.

swapEstimatedNetworkFeeSummary.description: $1 will be the translation of swapEstimatedNetworkFee, with the font bolded

swapFailedErrorDescriptionWithSupportLin.description: This message is shown to a user if their swap fails. The $1 will be replaced by support.metamask.io

swapFromTo.description: Tells a user that they need to confirm on their hardware wallet a swap of 2 tokens. $1 is a source token and $2 is a destination token

swapMaxNetworkFeeInfo.description: $1 will be the translation of swapMaxNetworkFees, with the font bolded

swapMistWalletFeeDescription.description: Provides information about the fee that metamask takes for swaps. $1 is a decimal number.

swapNQuotes.description: $1 is the number of quotes that the user can select from when opening the list of quotes on the 'view quote' screen

swapNewQuoteIn.description: Tells the user the amount of time until the currently displayed quotes are update. $1 is a time that is counting down from 1:00 to 0:00

swapOnceTransactionHasProcess.description: This message communicates the token that is being transferred. It is shown on the awaiting swap screen. The $1 will be a token symbol.

swapPriceDifference.description: This message represents the price slippage for the swap.  $1 and $4 are a number (ex: 2.89), $2 and $5 are symbols (ex: ETH), and $3 and $6 are fiat currency amounts.

swapPriceDifferenceTitle.description: $1 is a number (ex: 1.23) that represents the price difference.

swapQuoteIncludesRate.description: Provides information about the fee that metamask takes for swaps. $1 is a decimal number.

swapQuoteNofN.description: A count of loaded quotes shown to the user while they are waiting for quotes to be fetched. $1 is the number of quotes already loaded, and $2 is the total number of quotes to load.

swapTokenAvailable.description: This message is shown after a swap is successful and communicates the exact amount of tokens the user has received for a swap. The $1 is a decimal number of tokens followed by the token symbol.

swapTokenBalanceUnavailable.description: This message communicates to the user that their balance of a given token is currently unavailable. $1 will be replaced by a token symbol

swapTokenToToken.description: Used in the transaction display list to describe a swap. $1 and $2 are the symbols of tokens in involved in a swap.

swapTokenVerificationMessage.description: Points the user to Etherscan as a place they can verify information about a token. $1 is replaced with the translation for "Etherscan" followed by an info icon that shows more info on hover.

swapTokenVerificationSources.description: Indicates the number of token information sources that recognize the symbol + address. $1 is a decimal number.

swapVerifyTokenExplanation.description: This appears in a tooltip next to the verifyThisTokenOn message. It gives the user more information about why they should check the token on a block explorer. $1 will be the name or url of the block explorer, which will be the translation of 'etherscan' or a block explorer url specified for a custom network.

swapYourTokenBalance.description: Tells the user how much of a token they have in their balance. $1 is a decimal number amount of tokens, and $2 is a token symbol

swapsNotEnoughForTx.description: Tells the user that they don't have enough of a token for a proposed swap. $1 is a token symbol

toAddress.description: $1 is the address to include in the To label. It is typically shortened first using shortenAddress

troubleConnectingToWallet.description: $1 is the wallet device name; $2 is a link to wallet connection guide

troubleTokenBalances.description: Followed by a link (here) to view token balances

trustSiteApprovePermission.description: $1 is the url requesting permission and $2 is the symbol of the currency that the request is for

unrecognizedChain.description: $1 is a clickable link with text defined by the 'unrecognizedChanLinkText' key. The link will open to instructions for users to validate custom network details.

unrecognizedChainLinkText.description: Serves as link text for the 'unrecognizedChain' key. This text will be embedded inside the translation for that key.

verifyThisTokenDecimalOn.description: Points the user to etherscan as a place they can verify information about a token. $1 is replaced with the translation for "etherscan"

verifyThisTokenOn.description: Points the user to etherscan as a place they can verify information about a token. $1 is replaced with the translation for "etherscan"

verifyThisUnconfirmedTokenOn.description: Points the user to etherscan as a place they can verify information about a token. $1 is replaced with the translation for "etherscan"

whatsNew.description: This is the title of a popup that gives users notifications about new features and updates to MistWallet.

xOfY.description: $1 and $2 are intended to be two numbers, where $2 is a total, and $1 is a count towards that total

xOfYPending.description: $1 and $2 are intended to be two numbers, where $2 is a total number of pending confirmations, and $1 is a count towards that total
